com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle.abstraction
Class OracleOperator

java.lang.Object
  com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle.abstraction.OracleExpression
      com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle.abstraction.OracleOperator

public class OracleOperator
extends OracleExpression

Represents an operator as part of an oracle. Conceptually, it is different from an OracleComparator only in the sense that it can have a different type than just boolean, and is hence used to represent, for instance, arithmetic operations.

Like OracleComparator instances, operators are not type safe, but rely on KeY to make sure that the underlying formulas are already in such a state.

christopher
